{
  "texts": [
    "The control time step is set to 30 minutes, as a consequence, each control action is executed across a span of two simulation time steps.",
    "The EnergyPlus side of the co-simulation environment receives at each simulation time step control actions from the Python side.",
    "The EnergyPlus model implements the control action and generates outputs related to the thermal energy system (i.e., TES SOC), indoor environmental parameters (i.e., indoor air temperature), and supplementary data (i.e., total building electrical consumption) integrated within the state-space of the controller.",
    "Furthermore, the EnergyPlus model provides supplementary details, such as direct and diffuse solar irradiation, employed by the PV model to compute the PV power generation.",
    "The outputs from the EnergyPlus and information about the electricity price schedule are supplied as inputs to the Python side."
  ]
}